{
  "stem": "23090.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were not seders as we, even today-- seders were something that my father would lay down on two chairs and-- and as wonderful as seder was, and you got to get the prize and find the matzohs and so on, it was a-- it was a very trying thing, because it took forever, as I look at it today.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a long, long, long night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, of course, the cooking was outstanding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, we just never stopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and the wonderfulness of the lokshen and the [NON-ENGLISH] and the-- and the things that my mother would prepare for the seder, which was traditional, but then there was some above and beyond traditional.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was just another wonderful thing to look forward to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the only bad thing for a young child, it just took too long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Since we are not very patient as children, it took forever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But seders, as traditionally, my dad took it right from the first page to the last page and there were no shortcuts. and-- and that, too, was a wonderful, wonderful remembrance and tradition to me to remember.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Normally, it was our family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We would invite our-- our-- my dad would invite the brothers and the sisters and cousins.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we would-- we would-- you know, each family, I imagine, had-- my dad was sort of the leader, since he was the eldest, and the eldest, in those days, was more of the leader, in terms of you looked up to them to lead you on a religious basis.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we normally got the honor to do the seder.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so everyone would come to him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we had the-- the uncles and everybody at our house.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
